definition: president (of a country)/same as 總統|总统
big/huge/large/major/great/wide/deep/older (than)/oldest/eldest/greatly/very much/(dialect) father/father's elder or younger brother
see 大夫[dai4 fu5]
always/to assemble/gather/total/overall/head/chief/general/in every case
to gather/to unite/to unify/whole

sentences.english: And this president has even approved names of American citizens on that list.
sentences.chinese: 而且这个大总统甚至把一些美国公民也列入名单。

sentences.english: Guards watch one document, only know that the ordinary people dress was president.
sentences.chinese: 卫兵一看证件，才知道这个普通着装的人竟是大总统。

sentences.english: This palace was now the home of President Yuan.
sentences.chinese: 这座宫殿现在成为袁大总统的官邸。

sentences.english: After the victory of the Revolution, Dr. Sun Yat-sen as the provisional president.
sentences.chinese: 辛亥革命胜利后，孙中山当了临时大总统。

definition: Yuan Shikai (1859-1916), senior general of late Qing, subsequently warlord and self-proclaimed emperor of China
the Warlord government of Northern China that developed from the Qing Beiyang army 北洋軍閥|北洋军阀 after the Xinhai revolution of 1911
Xu Shichang (1855-1939), politician associated with the Northern Warlords, president of China in 1921
Duan Qirui (1864-1936), commander of Beiyang Army under Yuan Shikai, then politician and powerful warlord
Cao Kun (1862-1938), one of the Northern Warlords
Dr Sun Yat-sen (1866-1925), first president of the Republic of China and co-founder of the Guomintang 國民黨|国民党/same as 孫逸仙|孙逸仙
Tang Shaoyi (1862-1939), politician and diplomat
the Zhili faction of the Northern Warlords
provisional government
Manchu Restoration of 1917, an attempt by general 張勳|张勋[Zhanɡ1 Xun1] to reinstate the monarchy in China by restoring the abdicated emperor Puyi 溥儀|溥仪[Pu3 yi2] to the throne
north China army, a modernizing Western-style army set up during late Qing, and a breeding ground for the Northern Warlords after the Qinghai revolution
the Northern Warlords (1912-1927)
Beiyang faction of Northern Warlords
Feng Yuxiang (1882-1948), warlord during Republic of China, strongly critical of Chiang Kai-shek
Ni Sichong (1868-1924), general closely linked to Yuan Shikai 袁世凱|袁世凯 during his unsuccessful 1915 bid for Empire
autocratic monarchy/imperial regime
